# VibeCraft — Epic Fantasy Knight Fighter (Human Physique)
#
# Body composition: HUMAN KNIGHT (not Orc)
#
# Diet & lifestyle differences (informing muscle/fat distribution):
#   Human knight: disciplined diet (lean proteins, grains, vegetables),
#     daily martial training (swordplay, jousting, shield drills, formation
#     exercises) → lean athletic build, defined V-taper, low body fat
#   Orc (what we avoid): raw meat, ale, gruel, raiding/brawling lifestyle
#     → barrel torso, thick subcutaneous fat, no waist definition,
#     uniformly thick limbs, bull neck, hunched posture
#
# Human athletic V-taper: broad trained shoulders tapering to narrow
#   conditioned waist (waist ~65% of chest width from front view).
#   Front-to-back depth preserved (ribcage, spine, organs maintain volume).
#   This is the hallmark of a trained warrior vs a brutish brawler.
#
# Proportional system: Loomis 7.5-head canon with S-curve spine
# Anatomical basis: Gray's Anatomy, Kenhub, Anatomy for Sculptors, Proko
# Body mesh: single connected component, no disjoint parts
# Armor: separate overlay plates over continuous body form
#
# 1743 vertices, 3168 triangles
# Convention: Y-up, right-handed coordinate system
